The paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on improving the performance of tree-structured sentence encoding models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper introduces a new model that learns a global transformation from pre-trained word embeddings into matrices, which can be composed via matrix multiplication. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on the Stanford NLI corpus and the Multi-Genre NLI corpus, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
